<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-48-0963 </DOCNO><TEXT>For quantum field theories that do not satisfy the Wightman positivitycondition, a Hilbert space structure condition is proposed, which guaranteesa Krein structure for the space of states associated to the Wightmanfunctions. The analogous problem for the Schwinger function is also discussed,as well as the conditions that ensure the analytic continuation of aKrein structure in the Euclidean case and vice versa. The Gupta--Bleulerformulation of free quantum electrodynamics is discussed as an example.</TEXT></DOC>